  "text": "BCG treatment and peritoneal macrophage preparation ICR mice (n = 6/group/treatment/experiment) were injected intraperitoneally with 2 mg BCG (Shanghai Institute of Biological Products) or PBS on day 2 and day 10. Peritoneal exudate cells were harvested from these mice, and peritoneal macrophages were purified on days 4, 8, and 12 by washing cells from peritoneal cavity lavage with 5 ml of ice-cold, sterile PBS, according to a previously described protocol [CITATION_1] . The cells were distributed in DMEM supplemented with 10% FBS in six-well tissue culture plates (5 x 10 6 cells/ml) and incubated for 4 h. Non-adherent cells were removed by washing twice with Opti-MEM at 37°C in a 5% CO 2 incubator.",
